snippet.textDisplay: Car number plates would be good to use. They usually have a garage name on the number plate, usually with a postcode or area. As someone who has been to Kilve a lot this was rather painful to watch, what with his pronunciation of Kilve (it's not Kilv-a it's simply Kilv), then when it said Kilve many times and he was more focussed on it being near Bath and Bristol, I felt like screaming that he had the answer within the first couple minutes of him being there


*For anyone who doesn't know, Kilve is a little seaside town on the Bristol coast, it's mostly known for its rock pools as the beach is much more a stoney beach than a sandy one, and you're more likely to find dog walkers than tourists. It's also a rather nice place to go for campfires / bonfires as at nighttime you're not likely to get bombarded like other beaches


It's also often used as a residential place for school kids, I myself didn't go but my brother did when he was in year 6

The whole challenge would only be interesting if there was either a time limit or a limited radius of operation - afaik the geoguessr videos have a limited radius.
